1. In the bottom left corner of the screen, click into the "Type here to search"
 
2. Type "control panel" and click on the "Control Panel" app
 
3. In the window that pops up, in the top right will be "view by:" Make sure this says either large or small icons.
 
4. Find the icon that says "Mail" and click it
 
5. On the next window that pops up, click on "Profiles" at the bottom of the list.
 
6. When the profile window opens, if there is a profile in the list click on the profile and then click on "remove"
 
7. Click on "Add" to the left of "Remove" 
 
8. Name your profile whatever you would like and click "Ok"
 
9. The system should find your email automatically. If it doesn't then check your internet/vpn connection.
 
10. Click on next once it finds your email. 
 
11. The system will prompt you for your pin twice. Make sure you are choosing the longer of the two certs and putting in your pin correctly. 
*****If it asks you for your pin a third time CLOSE out of the program completely. Even if you put in your pin correctly and you do so a third time your CAC will be locked out and you will need to visit your local CAC office.********
 
12. Once the process finishes, the "finish" button should now be highlighted. Click it.
 
13. Open outlook.
